::Shadow Wing::

She looked at Lunarpine and nudged the crow closer to him. Knowing he 
can smell the crow, she still wanted to help him.  She hoped that she 
could help him with his optics.  She felt bad because she felt 
somewhat to blame for his injury. She was still a little mad at him 
for what he said about leaving the fighting to fighters. 
Right now, she just wanted to make a mends with him and hope that he 
would except the peace offering.

"It's a nice big crow I managed to catch.  Have dinner and we can 
head back to the base."  She smiled, "or we can stay out here and 
hang out under the stars tonight.  I don't mind either way."
She was glad he was still alive.  She felt a smile in her spark when 
she looked at him.  He was a strong, couragous fighter, who cared for 
his friends.  She was believing her spark was really falling for 
him.  She asked herself, how else could a bot get such strong 
reactions out of her is she didn't care for them.
